headline: Oracle Supports White House's Vision for Healthcare Data Interoperability
summary: Oracle today pledged support for the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services' Digital Health Ecosystem and Interoperability Framework. During the Make Health Tech Great Again event at the White House, Oracle executives Mike Sicilia and Seema Verma committed to working with the federal government and industry leaders to deliver a more interoperable, secure, AI-enabled healthcare system that improves patient care, enhances provider experiences, and drives down the cost of care delivery.
